WEBVTT

00:00:09.720 --> 00:00:11.600
Deprived urban areas

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:13.920
on the edges of large cities:

00:00:14.120 --> 00:00:17.920
in Belgium, France,
Great Britain.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:21.880
Middle-class cities:

00:00:22.080 --> 00:00:24.560
in Denmark and Germany.

00:00:25.640 --> 00:00:28.960
These very different areas
have one thing in common:

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:34.080
for 30 years, their names have been
listed on the maps of an

00:00:34.280 --> 00:00:38.520
ultra-minority, but continually
expanding Islamic ideology:

00:00:38.720 --> 00:00:40.080
jihadism.

00:00:43.200 --> 00:00:44.280
The first to preach

00:00:44.800 --> 00:00:46.520
100% European terrorism,

00:00:47.240 --> 00:00:51.040
this totalitarian ideology has led
to more and more deadly projects.

00:00:51.680 --> 00:00:52.960
We're going to kill all Americans!

00:00:53.640 --> 00:00:54.760
Since 2001,

00:00:54.960 --> 00:00:57.880
150 attacks have been carried
out on the Old Continent,

00:00:58.200 --> 00:01:01.000
to which countless victims in
Muslim countries can be added.

00:01:08.400 --> 00:01:10.160
From the end of the '80s,

00:01:10.360 --> 00:01:14.040
a handful of ideologists from
the Middle East settled in Europe

00:01:14.240 --> 00:01:16.480
and propagated jihadist thinking.

00:01:18.320 --> 00:01:22.640
Following their steps means tracing
the origins of a political project

00:01:22.840 --> 00:01:27.480
which European democracies have
had difficulty understanding.

00:01:46.920 --> 00:01:49.640
In November 1989, no one

00:01:49.840 --> 00:01:51.760
cared about the jihadist phenomenon.

00:01:52.960 --> 00:01:54.960
The word couldn't even be found
in dictionaries yet.

00:01:56.800 --> 00:01:59.760
Eyes were turned towards Berlin
and the shameful wall

00:02:00.240 --> 00:02:04.680
that people were knocking down
with hammers and shouts of liberty.

00:02:08.680 --> 00:02:11.200
I was rooted in the emotion
of the moment

00:02:11.400 --> 00:02:13.640
because my father was German,

00:02:13.840 --> 00:02:16.680
so for me, it was
a triumph of humanity.

00:02:17.040 --> 00:02:19.600
It was the triumph of people.
People power.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:29.640
And it dawned on me at that moment
that one of the reasons this was

00:02:29.840 --> 00:02:33.560
happening was because the Russians
and the Soviets are withdrawing.

00:02:33.880 --> 00:02:36.160
Of course, Afghanistan was
happening at the same time,

00:02:36.480 --> 00:02:40.400
so in other words,
1989 wasn't just about Europe.

00:02:44.760 --> 00:02:48.960
During previous months, the Soviet
troops pulled out of Afghanistan,

00:02:49.160 --> 00:02:52.520
hastening the end
of the Cold War in their rout.

00:02:55.160 --> 00:02:56.080
In the face of this defeated army,

00:02:57.080 --> 00:03:01.000
Western regimes dreamt of the
victory of their democratic model.

00:03:02.240 --> 00:03:04.800
They didn't see the other half
of the scenario:

00:03:06.360 --> 00:03:10.520
The jihadist movement was born
in the gaps of this Afghan conflict.

00:03:11.360 --> 00:03:14.720
Its story had begun
10 years before.

00:03:19.920 --> 00:03:23.320
In 1979, Soviet troops
entered Kabul,

00:03:23.520 --> 00:03:25.080
the capital of Afghanistan.

00:03:27.520 --> 00:03:30.120
The Russians wanted to impose
a communist regime.

00:03:30.320 --> 00:03:33.400
THE AFGHAN CRISIS
FROM REBELLION TO RESISTANCE

00:03:37.800 --> 00:03:40.880
Afghan resistance organised itself
against them,

00:03:41.880 --> 00:03:45.440
simple peasants, young students and
former soldiers took up arms.

00:03:49.560 --> 00:03:53.120
Abroad, acts of war by these
ill-equipped Mujaheddin

00:03:53.320 --> 00:03:56.200
affronting one of the most powerful
armies in the world resonated.

00:04:00.760 --> 00:04:05.280
Thousands in Arab countries
wanted to join the Afghan front.

00:04:07.840 --> 00:04:10.120
One man participated
in their mobilisation

00:04:10.720 --> 00:04:14.360
and played a central role in the
emergence of the jihadist movement:

00:04:16.960 --> 00:04:20.640
Abdallah Azzam,
a Jordanian of Palestinian origin.

00:04:23.840 --> 00:04:27.240
This doctor in Quranic law was
close to the Muslim Brotherhood,

00:04:27.440 --> 00:04:31.440
a vast Islamic political movement,
very influential in the Arab world.

00:04:32.400 --> 00:04:35.840
His charisma and violent preaching
against Israel and the West

00:04:36.040 --> 00:04:37.760
had forced him into exile.

00:04:40.480 --> 00:04:43.240
When the Soviet troops
entered Kabul,

00:04:43.440 --> 00:04:45.160
he spoke to the Muslim world.

00:04:47.360 --> 00:04:48.760
I was a university professor.

00:04:49.640 --> 00:04:51.560
I lived just next to Mecca,

00:04:52.040 --> 00:04:55.360
but God knows

00:04:55.960 --> 00:04:57.680
how I prefer these assemblies

00:04:58.560 --> 00:05:00.760
to years of living

00:05:01.640 --> 00:05:04.960
in Mecca.

00:05:05.400 --> 00:05:09.680
Abdallah Azzam is in many ways
the father of the modern jihad.

00:05:09.880 --> 00:05:12.880
His writings and his lectures

00:05:13.320 --> 00:05:16.120
really laid out the principles

00:05:16.320 --> 00:05:19.040
that was the duty of every Muslim

00:05:19.240 --> 00:05:21.800
to engage in jihad war against

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:25.680
foreign armies invading Islam

00:05:26.640 --> 00:05:30.000
and he put at the top of that list
Israel and the Palestinians.

00:05:31.240 --> 00:05:34.960
But the target that was
available was

00:05:35.160 --> 00:05:37.640
the Soviet Union in Afghanistan.

00:05:38.440 --> 00:05:39.920
He said:
"Don't listen to the leaders.

00:05:40.400 --> 00:05:42.120
Don't listen to your local imam.

00:05:42.320 --> 00:05:44.360
Don't listen to your parents.

00:05:44.800 --> 00:05:47.960
They're going to tell you that you
should wait or leave it in the hands

00:05:48.280 --> 00:05:50.920
of officials, but don't listen
to them. Just go.

00:05:51.240 --> 00:05:54.040
And God will punish you, in fact,

00:05:54.240 --> 00:05:57.600
if you don't go and he will reward
you handsomely if you do."

00:05:59.880 --> 00:06:03.960
The Islamist intellectual became
a link between the Afghan Mujaheddin

00:06:04.160 --> 00:06:06.000
and their international support.

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:12.400
From Peshawar, a Pakistani city
on the Afghan border,

00:06:13.920 --> 00:06:18.000
from 1984 he organised the reception
of former foreign soldiers,

00:06:18.200 --> 00:06:21.160
now known as "Arab Afghans".

00:06:24.280 --> 00:06:27.800
The first thing he did was
to set up an infrastructure

00:06:28.120 --> 00:06:30.360
to help people find their way

00:06:30.560 --> 00:06:34.360
and to help people get settled
in Peshawar,

00:06:34.880 --> 00:06:38.640
and he set up the so-called
Services Bureau.

00:06:40.360 --> 00:06:43.240
The Services Bureau in Peshawar:

00:06:43.440 --> 00:06:47.200
a legendary name
for today's jihadists.

00:06:50.720 --> 00:06:54.880
Algerian Abdullah Anas was one of
the first to walk through its door.

00:06:56.200 --> 00:07:00.040
At 23, he became Abdallah Azzam's
right-hand man,

00:07:00.920 --> 00:07:02.800
even marrying his daughter.

00:07:04.480 --> 00:07:06.040
The Services Bureau wants you

00:07:06.240 --> 00:07:09.560
to know how can you help
in Afghanistan,

00:07:09.760 --> 00:07:11.640
whether you are a doctor,
you are a teacher,

00:07:11.840 --> 00:07:14.440
you are a driver, you are a chef
to cook,

00:07:14.640 --> 00:07:17.360
you are mullah, you are
"aâlem", you are scholar,

00:07:17.560 --> 00:07:18.240
whatever you are...

00:07:18.560 --> 00:07:24.160
Just give what you have to
Afghanistan, to the Afghani people.

00:07:26.360 --> 00:07:28.400
Most of them
never crossed the border.

00:07:29.240 --> 00:07:32.240
They just came and stayed
for a while and

00:07:32.440 --> 00:07:35.920
absorbed Abdullah Azzam's message.

00:07:36.240 --> 00:07:38.720
He wanted them to be
indoctrinated with

00:07:38.920 --> 00:07:41.880
the philosophy of the jihad
that he was promoting, and

00:07:42.080 --> 00:07:46.680
this gave him the perfect venue
for doing that.

00:07:49.880 --> 00:07:50.960
The Services Bureau saw

00:07:51.320 --> 00:07:54.200
a stream of those who,
a decade later,

00:07:54.400 --> 00:07:57.440
would become the faces of
international terrorism,

00:07:59.240 --> 00:08:03.840
like this Saudi man, son of a rich
family of entrepreneurial builders,

00:08:04.040 --> 00:08:05.720
Osama bin Laden.

00:08:07.880 --> 00:08:11.280
Osama bin Laden
joined the Services Bureau

00:08:11.480 --> 00:08:14.720
after it was established,
one year after that.

00:08:15.160 --> 00:08:19.520
So, he used to give, I think,
5 to 10,000 dollars every month

00:08:19.920 --> 00:08:24.520
for Sheikh Abdullah Azam
to run the guest house.

00:08:28.880 --> 00:08:30.480
In the middle of the '80s,

00:08:30.680 --> 00:08:34.520
American President Ronald Reagan
armed the Afghan Mujaheddin,

00:08:34.720 --> 00:08:37.080
in the name of the right against
communism.

00:08:39.280 --> 00:08:44.120
He wasn't worried about these
radical Islamists supporting him.

00:08:51.640 --> 00:08:55.240
Abdallah Azzam then travelled to
the United States every two years,

00:08:56.880 --> 00:09:00.200
travelling freely
and preaching jihad,

00:09:00.400 --> 00:09:02.280
like in this Brooklyn mosque.

00:09:02.480 --> 00:09:06.760
Our speaker today is

00:09:06.960 --> 00:09:09.640
Sheikh Abdallah Azzam.

00:09:09.840 --> 00:09:13.520
Whoever wants to carry out jihad
in the way of Allah,

00:09:13.720 --> 00:09:15.960
should join him.

00:09:17.680 --> 00:09:20.760
Abdallah Azzam himself
legitimised attacks

00:09:20.960 --> 00:09:23.920
on Jewish targets in America.

00:09:24.840 --> 00:09:29.600
The word jihad means
"fight in the way of God."

00:09:29.800 --> 00:09:33.560
It comes down to their being
viewed as just a minor phenomenon

00:09:33.760 --> 00:09:37.160
and perhaps also people not really
reading what they were writing

00:09:37.360 --> 00:09:39.120
or listening to what they were
saying, because

00:09:39.640 --> 00:09:40.640
if they had,

00:09:40.840 --> 00:09:45.040
they would have noticed
the seeds of future trouble.

00:09:46.480 --> 00:09:48.960
All the unbelievers control us:

00:09:49.760 --> 00:09:52.800
the Americans, the English...

00:09:53.560 --> 00:09:57.480
And behind them, the hands
of world Judaism,

00:09:58.480 --> 00:10:01.480
with its money, its women
and its media.

00:10:02.400 --> 00:10:06.600
Muslims coming to the United States
to raise money for causes was

00:10:06.800 --> 00:10:09.400
not something the FBI monitored.

00:10:09.720 --> 00:10:11.960
He wanted to raise money
for a war that

00:10:12.160 --> 00:10:13.800
we were already paying for.

00:10:14.000 --> 00:10:18.360
So all the better! If someone
else wants to pay for it,

00:10:19.080 --> 00:10:21.240
it saves
the American taxpayer money.

00:10:24.720 --> 00:10:29.160
In Europe too, Abdallah Azzam's
radical thinking was appearing.

00:10:29.880 --> 00:10:32.760
His magazine Al Jihad was
distributed in London,

00:10:32.960 --> 00:10:35.680
Paris, Copenhagen and Brussels.

00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:40.760
It was discovered that these people
had an official office in Belgium

00:10:40.960 --> 00:10:43.400
with a number in the phone book

00:10:43.600 --> 00:10:45.720
on one of the largest avenues in
Brussels, Avenue de Tervueren,

00:10:45.920 --> 00:10:48.960
and there was a lot of fund-raising
for these people.

00:10:50.640 --> 00:10:52.400
Somewhere, it's true
that it's a little intriguing,

00:10:52.600 --> 00:10:56.160
as these people are, how shall I put
it, a sort of religious peculiarity.

00:10:58.200 --> 00:11:00.600
They were helped by the Americans,
so they couldn't be as bad as that,

00:11:00.800 --> 00:11:02.520
but we realised that they weren't
from here.

00:11:02.720 --> 00:11:07.440
But we didn't see that this
could lead to problems later on.

00:11:09.800 --> 00:11:11.400
No one knows how many Europeans

00:11:11.560 --> 00:11:14.000
responded to
the Afghan jihad call in the '80s.

00:11:15.680 --> 00:11:17.640
Several dozen, more or less.

00:11:22.280 --> 00:11:24.080
Usama Hasam is one of them.

00:11:24.720 --> 00:11:27.840
He grew up in a working class
district in East London.

00:11:28.720 --> 00:11:30.840
From a line of renowned imams,

00:11:31.040 --> 00:11:33.640
he memorised the Quran
at the age of 11.

00:11:39.200 --> 00:11:42.320
He had just entered a prestigious
English university

00:11:42.520 --> 00:11:46.760
and made use of a family visit to
Pakistan to join the Afghan front.

00:11:47.960 --> 00:11:54.200
My grandad and uncles were delighted
that their nephew or grandson from

00:11:54.400 --> 00:11:56.320
London was coming for jihad.

00:11:56.520 --> 00:12:00.560
My uncle even said: "You know,
you're an example to us.

00:12:00.760 --> 00:12:02.880
We're sitting here next door
to the jihad and we've

00:12:03.080 --> 00:12:04.040
not taken part."

00:12:09.640 --> 00:12:12.200
Usually the mujaheddin, you would
have to do six months' training

00:12:12.400 --> 00:12:14.480
before they allowed you anywhere
near the front line.

00:12:14.640 --> 00:12:17.400
They had a proper system
of training.

00:12:17.600 --> 00:12:21.680
But to see three men
with long beards

00:12:22.480 --> 00:12:25.040
come from London,
knowing the Quran...

00:12:25.440 --> 00:12:28.440
And they let us. They gave us
special permission. They liked us

00:12:28.640 --> 00:12:32.200
a lot, so we spent 24 hours
on the front line,

00:12:32.400 --> 00:12:33.720
just one day and one night.

00:12:36.760 --> 00:12:41.080
On his return to London, Usama was
welcomed as a hero by his family.

00:12:42.000 --> 00:12:43.920
Many wanted
to hear his story, no matter

00:12:44.120 --> 00:12:46.680
if he had only spent a short time
on the front.

00:12:48.480 --> 00:12:52.120
The vast majority of what we call
the Afghan Arabs

00:12:52.320 --> 00:12:55.400
were there
to get their picture taken,

00:12:55.720 --> 00:12:57.880
but the realities of what they did
on the ground

00:12:58.080 --> 00:13:01.720
are much less important than
the mythology that they developed,

00:13:01.920 --> 00:13:05.440
which was that they defeated
the Soviet Union,

00:13:05.640 --> 00:13:09.960
that foreign fighters were
the decisive tipping point.

00:13:10.160 --> 00:13:12.720
That's all untrue.

00:13:14.120 --> 00:13:16.440
In Peshawar, in 1987,

00:13:16.640 --> 00:13:18.120
the first ideological differences

00:13:18.280 --> 00:13:20.760
appeared among
Abdallah Azzam's disciples.

00:13:22.760 --> 00:13:27.400
Osama bin Laden wanted to take
jihad to an international level.

00:13:28.040 --> 00:13:30.120
And then suddenly,
one day he decided:

00:13:30.320 --> 00:13:33.800
"I'm not going to spend a penny
for the Services Bureau.

00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:38.760
I'm going to establish my own
guest house, my own training camp.

00:13:39.080 --> 00:13:43.480
We should form a small unit

00:13:43.680 --> 00:13:46.400
to fight outside of Afghanistan".

00:13:46.920 --> 00:13:50.360
And then we saw at the end
where it led.

00:13:53.920 --> 00:13:55.920
As a result of this split,

00:13:56.400 --> 00:13:59.360
the Al Qaeda organisation
was created.

00:14:04.000 --> 00:14:05.640
In 1989,

00:14:05.960 --> 00:14:08.520
while the Soviet troops were
leaving Afghanistan,

00:14:08.720 --> 00:14:11.160
Abdallah Azzam,
father of the jihad,

00:14:11.360 --> 00:14:15.120
was killed by a car bomb
in Peshawar.

00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:21.160
For his son-in-law Abdallah Anas,
a page had turned.

00:14:21.360 --> 00:14:25.560
He left Pakistan for a long journey
which took him to London.

00:14:26.920 --> 00:14:28.960
From the beginning, we said:

00:14:29.160 --> 00:14:33.960
"Come on. We came to Afghanistan
to help the Afghans

00:14:34.520 --> 00:14:38.160
just to kick out the Red Army.

00:14:38.360 --> 00:14:41.720
When that is finished,
so jihad is finished."

00:14:47.280 --> 00:14:50.920
This point of view was not greeted
unanimously by the Afghan Arabs.

00:14:51.640 --> 00:14:53.800
Some wanted to continue the jihad,

00:14:54.000 --> 00:14:56.360
freeing other Muslim countries.

00:14:57.400 --> 00:15:00.840
KABUL, AFGHANISTAN

00:15:02.560 --> 00:15:06.480
A conflict in the heart of Europe
gave them the opportunity.

00:15:06.680 --> 00:15:09.680
SARAJEVO, BOSNIA

00:15:09.880 --> 00:15:13.080
The multi-faith state
of Bosnia-Herzegovina

00:15:13.280 --> 00:15:16.560
had been caught up in a civil war
since the explosion of Yugoslavia.

00:15:16.760 --> 00:15:20.320
BOSNIA IS HELL

00:15:22.560 --> 00:15:24.640
Sarajevo, its capital,

00:15:24.960 --> 00:15:28.280
had become the symbol of a majority
Muslim population

00:15:28.480 --> 00:15:31.720
trapped by a Christian
Serbian militia.

00:15:35.520 --> 00:15:39.160
For some Afghan Arabs,
a new jihad had begun.

00:15:39.560 --> 00:15:42.320
They wanted to help these
ill-equipped Muslim fighters

00:15:42.520 --> 00:15:43.800
who were resisting as well
as they could,

00:16:01.200 --> 00:16:02.880
especially as in the Serbian zone,

00:16:03.080 --> 00:16:06.000
Bosnian Muslims had been
herded into camps

00:16:06.200 --> 00:16:07.720
where they were
starved and tortured,

00:16:08.960 --> 00:16:11.120
the first suspicion
of ethnic cleansing.

00:16:14.320 --> 00:16:15.840
The Afghan Arabs
mobilised themselves

00:16:16.040 --> 00:16:19.600
and arrived in Bosnia, from where
they reached the town of Zenica.

00:16:22.920 --> 00:16:26.040
From the month of August 1992,

00:16:26.240 --> 00:16:29.040
they appeared
in combat uniform,

00:16:29.240 --> 00:16:31.640
weapons in their hands.

00:16:32.040 --> 00:16:36.920
They started to incite

00:16:37.120 --> 00:16:38.920
people to join the fight.

00:16:39.120 --> 00:16:41.280
They declared that they had
come to defend

00:16:41.480 --> 00:16:44.560
Bosnia-Herzegovina and

00:16:44.760 --> 00:16:49.480
to save their Muslim brothers.

00:16:49.680 --> 00:16:52.800
At the beginning, the people
found them very nice.

00:16:57.360 --> 00:16:59.600
These men were welcomed
with open arms

00:16:59.800 --> 00:17:02.520
by the Bosnian president,
Alija Izetbegović.

00:17:05.680 --> 00:17:08.000
They were considered to be
experienced soldiers

00:17:08.200 --> 00:17:10.960
and were incorporated
into the Bosnian army.

00:17:11.160 --> 00:17:14.000
Attention! At ease!

00:17:15.400 --> 00:17:17.880
JIHAD

00:17:18.600 --> 00:17:22.720
Bosnia was the subject of extra-
ordinary jihadist propaganda

00:17:22.920 --> 00:17:24.760
broadcast via video cassette.

00:17:25.920 --> 00:17:27.360
The mountains were liberated

00:17:27.560 --> 00:17:30.200
and the mujaheddin
continued advancing

00:17:30.400 --> 00:17:32.840
until they reached
some difficult territory.

00:17:33.240 --> 00:17:37.880
The fighting continued from morning
until the time of Asr prayer.

00:17:43.480 --> 00:17:46.920
The Afghan Arabs
had a society project:

00:17:47.120 --> 00:17:49.800
to set up an Islamic state
in Bosnia.

00:17:51.680 --> 00:17:54.560
In remote villages,
they imposed Sharia law.

00:18:02.560 --> 00:18:05.760
In Bosnia, Sharia law
and strict Islamic rules

00:18:05.960 --> 00:18:08.240
were not followed.

00:18:08.440 --> 00:18:10.280
People respected custom:

00:18:10.480 --> 00:18:14.800
they went to the mosque,

00:18:15.280 --> 00:18:17.680
some did Ramadan,

00:18:17.880 --> 00:18:20.880
but no one worried about clothing

00:18:21.080 --> 00:18:24.360
or rules regarding prayer or
that kind of thing.

00:18:25.200 --> 00:18:28.800
Personally, I had
worries about that.

00:18:29.000 --> 00:18:32.600
My wife dressed as a European.

00:18:32.800 --> 00:18:35.640
And as they knew very well
that I was commanding

00:18:35.840 --> 00:18:37.720
one of the largest brigades
in the territory,

00:18:38.200 --> 00:18:41.800
one day they threw eggs at us,

00:18:42.000 --> 00:18:43.880
at my wife and I,

00:18:44.080 --> 00:18:46.720
because she was wearing European
clothes and we were holding hands.

00:18:53.120 --> 00:18:56.240
Cohabitation with the Bosnian army
went badly.

00:18:57.480 --> 00:18:59.360
In 1993, the Afghan Arabs

00:18:59.560 --> 00:19:03.160
obtained the creation
of an independent brigade:

00:19:03.360 --> 00:19:05.640
the "El Mujaheddin" brigade.

00:19:05.920 --> 00:19:08.720
It set up camp
in the Serbian zone.

00:19:14.960 --> 00:19:17.560
In this valley,
where the fighting raged,

00:19:17.760 --> 00:19:21.920
the jihadists committed terrible
atrocities against the Serbs,

00:19:22.120 --> 00:19:24.280
whether civil or military.

00:19:26.560 --> 00:19:29.760
I was in the Serbian
Republican Army,

00:19:30.600 --> 00:19:32.680
leading one of the brigades

00:19:33.080 --> 00:19:34.560
that was attacked
by the El Mujaheddin unit.

00:19:35.160 --> 00:19:36.920
I'm going to tell you something:

00:19:37.960 --> 00:19:40.400
When they take a Serbian soldier

00:19:40.960 --> 00:19:44.480
in the trenches,

00:19:44.680 --> 00:19:47.440
they cut off his head and

00:19:47.760 --> 00:19:49.360
set it next to the body...

00:19:49.560 --> 00:19:51.280
In your opinion,

00:19:51.480 --> 00:19:55.040
what does the soldier's comrade

00:19:55.240 --> 00:19:58.000
feel seeing
his colleague's decapitated head?

00:19:58.200 --> 00:20:00.720
It's particularly atrocious.
We had never seen that.

00:20:01.040 --> 00:20:02.960
EL MUJAHEDDIN, 1993

00:20:04.480 --> 00:20:07.480
Atrocious scenes,
meticulously filmed.

00:20:20.400 --> 00:20:22.360
In the brigade's camp,

00:20:22.560 --> 00:20:26.360
more than 50 soldiers and
civilians were executed,

00:20:26.560 --> 00:20:29.880
their heads decapitated and
brandished like trophies.

00:20:38.440 --> 00:20:42.240
The Mujaheddin even played football
with one of them.

00:20:43.640 --> 00:20:46.920
The Mujaheddin played football

00:20:47.120 --> 00:20:49.040
with the brothers in the army.

00:20:49.240 --> 00:20:51.520
It was a game full of love

00:20:51.720 --> 00:20:53.960
and friendship in the name of Allah,

00:20:54.160 --> 00:20:56.280
with no hatred or bad feeling.

00:21:04.800 --> 00:21:07.760
These atrocities went unnoticed
among the mass crimes

00:21:07.960 --> 00:21:09.840
committed by the Serb units.

00:21:14.040 --> 00:21:16.920
In Srebrenica, under the gaze of
the Blue Berets,

00:21:17.120 --> 00:21:19.840
the Serbs separated the women
and children from the men.

00:21:22.680 --> 00:21:25.600
The men were taken away
and massacred.

00:21:39.680 --> 00:21:42.600
This massacre
of more than 8000 Muslims

00:21:42.800 --> 00:21:45.080
set international opinion
in turmoil.

00:21:46.760 --> 00:21:50.280
In Europe, radical Islamist groups
took advantage of it

00:21:50.480 --> 00:21:53.480
to instrumentalise the anger
of young Muslims.

00:21:55.160 --> 00:21:58.040
There were talks
and presentations every week.

00:21:58.680 --> 00:21:59.720
I went to one

00:21:59.920 --> 00:22:04.080
in South London, a mosque. A friend
of mine from our movement who had

00:22:04.280 --> 00:22:06.440
been to Bosnia and come back and
he showed this graphic video

00:22:06.640 --> 00:22:10.800
including Bosnian Muslims being
slaughtered, a baby being strangled.

00:22:13.440 --> 00:22:16.360
At this time, Usama
was preaching jihad

00:22:16.560 --> 00:22:18.680
to students in Great Britain.

00:22:19.680 --> 00:22:22.800
At the end of a meeting,
a man challenged him.

00:22:24.680 --> 00:22:26.480
He came up to me afterwards
and he said:

00:22:26.800 --> 00:22:28.040
"That was all very good, but

00:22:28.240 --> 00:22:30.840
what about the reality of Bosnia?
Muslims are dying.

00:22:32.800 --> 00:22:34.800
What are we doing to support them?"

00:22:35.160 --> 00:22:36.720
And I said to him: "Well,

00:22:37.880 --> 00:22:40.200
if you really want to help, you can
go and fight there."

00:22:40.480 --> 00:22:41.720
And he said: "Really?"

00:22:41.920 --> 00:22:43.280
I said: "Yeah, jihad."
And he said:

00:22:43.480 --> 00:22:46.880
"What? It's possible to go for jihad
in Bosnia?" and I said: "Yeah."

00:22:47.200 --> 00:22:49.840
He said: "Who do I contact?"
I gave him two names.

00:22:50.560 --> 00:22:52.440
I come from South London.

00:22:53.080 --> 00:22:54.880
I'm 21 years old.

00:22:55.080 --> 00:22:58.560
I'm a third year medical student
in Birmingham University,

00:22:58.760 --> 00:23:01.040
and I live in Golders Green, London.

00:23:01.440 --> 00:23:03.720
If you want to see true people,
true Muslims with unity,

00:23:03.920 --> 00:23:05.880
you need to come to this place.

00:23:06.200 --> 00:23:07.280
Every time I'm in Britain,

00:23:07.480 --> 00:23:10.440
I go to study circles,
I go to lectures, I go to talks and

00:23:10.640 --> 00:23:12.880
I feel in my heart that something
is empty.

00:23:13.080 --> 00:23:15.600
I watched the TV and tears roll
down my face when

00:23:15.800 --> 00:23:18.280
I see the Muslims in Bosnia,
Muslims in Palestine.

00:23:18.480 --> 00:23:21.680
And then I come here and you feel
a sense of satisfaction.

00:23:21.880 --> 00:23:23.880
You feel that you are fulfilling
your duty.

00:23:24.080 --> 00:23:28.200
Great Britain apparently supplied
one of the largest contingents of

00:23:28.400 --> 00:23:29.920
fighters in Bosnia,

00:23:30.120 --> 00:23:32.120
a phenomenon
which surprised no one.

00:23:36.960 --> 00:23:39.160
In the middle of the '90s,

00:23:39.360 --> 00:23:43.480
jihadist ideology had already
spread to the London working class

00:23:43.680 --> 00:23:46.640
through a handful
of radical preachers.

00:23:48.240 --> 00:23:50.960
These activists, threatened
in their home countries,

00:23:51.120 --> 00:23:52.920
had obtained a right of asylum,

00:23:53.120 --> 00:23:56.240
just like thousands
of political opponents in Europe.

00:23:56.920 --> 00:23:58.200
Contrary to the latter,

00:23:58.560 --> 00:24:01.920
they advocated jihad
in the British capital,

00:24:02.120 --> 00:24:05.720
to the point of earning it
the nickname of "Londonistan".

00:24:09.040 --> 00:24:13.760
London in the late 1990s
and early 2000s became

00:24:13.960 --> 00:24:18.040
a hub of activity for jihadists.

00:24:18.560 --> 00:24:20.160
They found a safe haven here.

00:24:20.360 --> 00:24:24.480
They found a way in which
they could propagate their ideas,

00:24:24.680 --> 00:24:25.800
find money

00:24:26.000 --> 00:24:30.600
and support
the wider Islamic movement.

00:24:31.120 --> 00:24:33.120
And the British government
in the 1990s

00:24:33.320 --> 00:24:36.440
had a very tolerant attitude
about this.

00:24:36.640 --> 00:24:39.960
As long as you didn't
get very specific

00:24:40.360 --> 00:24:43.760
about the kind of violence
you wanted to carry out,

00:24:45.240 --> 00:24:47.280
the British
basically let you do it.

00:24:47.680 --> 00:24:50.600
I don't think it was a strategy.
I think it was a miscalculation.

00:24:55.840 --> 00:25:00.080
The English branch of Hizb Ut
tahrir, an Islamist organisation,

00:25:00.400 --> 00:25:03.040
counted thousands
of British Muslims itself alone.

00:25:04.760 --> 00:25:07.320
Its plan was to re-establish
the Khalifat

00:25:07.760 --> 00:25:09.680
and impose Sharia law
in the Arab world.

00:25:15.240 --> 00:25:18.160
Its leaders denounced
the Western way of life,

00:25:18.360 --> 00:25:19.960
its democratic principles,

00:25:20.160 --> 00:25:23.560
and spread anti-Jewish, misogynistic
and homophobic rhetoric

00:25:23.760 --> 00:25:25.320
which did not move many people
in the United Kingdom.

00:25:25.640 --> 00:25:27.600
In Iran, since 1980, over 4000

00:25:27.800 --> 00:25:30.400
lesbians and gay men have

00:25:30.600 --> 00:25:32.720
been executed
by the Islamic authorities.

00:25:35.680 --> 00:25:39.640
Hizb Ut-tahrir led a field campaign
at universities

00:25:39.840 --> 00:25:42.080
and even at public schools.

00:25:45.760 --> 00:25:49.720
This was how Rashad Ali,
then a young schoolboy of 14,

00:25:49.920 --> 00:25:54.440
first met members of
the organisation among his teachers.

00:25:56.560 --> 00:25:58.920
They shook everything I believed in

00:25:59.560 --> 00:26:00.840
and they reshaped it new.

00:26:01.040 --> 00:26:01.840
RASHAD ALI
FORMER HIZB UT-TAHRIR EXECUTIVE

00:26:02.040 --> 00:26:06.160
So, I now no longer knew what
religion was.

00:26:07.000 --> 00:26:08.400
It wasn't just something
in the background.

00:26:08.560 --> 00:26:10.880
It wasn't just something
to do with my religious faith.

00:26:11.200 --> 00:26:12.720
It was an ideology.

00:26:17.160 --> 00:26:19.120
It is an ideology
that's totalitarian.

00:26:19.520 --> 00:26:22.000
It was revolutionary and aimed
at changing the entire world

00:26:22.160 --> 00:26:24.040
and I was part of that.

00:26:28.520 --> 00:26:32.880
The founder of the English branch of
Hizb ut-tahrir was Omar Bakri,

00:26:33.080 --> 00:26:35.680
a Syrian Islamist opponent
living in London as a refugee

00:26:35.840 --> 00:26:37.160
since the 1980s.

00:26:38.320 --> 00:26:42.320
He has been part of the European
jihadist scene up to today.

00:26:47.120 --> 00:26:48.880
In 1996,

00:26:49.080 --> 00:26:52.640
Omar Bakri broke away from Hizb Ut-
tahrir, which he found too moderate.

00:26:54.960 --> 00:26:58.800
He created his own organisation,
Al-Muhajiroun.

00:26:59.560 --> 00:27:03.080
He wanted to establish an Islamic
state in the heart of Europe.

00:27:08.400 --> 00:27:11.600
Omar Bakri is often quoted as saying

00:27:11.800 --> 00:27:14.520
he wanted to see the black flag

00:27:14.720 --> 00:27:16.760
of Islam flying over Downing Street.

00:27:19.280 --> 00:27:21.600
One day, Islamic State is going to
be established in a Muslim country,

00:27:21.800 --> 00:27:25.320
maybe in Europe, maybe in France,
maybe in Britain, God knows,

00:27:25.720 --> 00:27:27.720
And if it's established outside,
it's got to conquer.

00:27:38.040 --> 00:27:41.520
The idea that a khalifat is
the only solution for Muslims,

00:27:41.720 --> 00:27:43.560
I think it's just nonsense now.

00:27:43.760 --> 00:27:45.280
But at the time, I believed it.

00:27:45.440 --> 00:27:47.880
It was a very interesting,
radical political idea.

00:27:48.280 --> 00:27:51.200
Another view that the only
solution is armed jihad, right?

00:27:51.400 --> 00:27:54.280
This was crazy and violent,
but it had a certain appeal.

00:27:57.360 --> 00:28:01.120
This radical rhetoric
attracted new followers.

00:28:03.240 --> 00:28:07.040
Abu Hamza al Masri, a former
nightclub bouncer,

00:28:07.240 --> 00:28:09.840
became a recognised figure
of Londonistan.

00:28:12.120 --> 00:28:16.760
Abu Hamza was rising in that
community as a spokesperson

00:28:17.000 --> 00:28:21.520
for the anger of many young men

00:28:21.720 --> 00:28:23.920
who had found themselves unemployed,

00:28:24.120 --> 00:28:29.120
who had found themselves
alienated from British society.

00:28:29.680 --> 00:28:31.640
It wasn't, you know,
highfalutin language.

00:28:31.840 --> 00:28:35.560
It was like: "I'll come and sock
them. We'll show them who's boss."

00:28:35.760 --> 00:28:39.920
So he wasn't frightened and had no
fear of saying controversial things.

00:28:40.120 --> 00:28:42.120
In fact, he thrived
on being controversial.

00:28:43.600 --> 00:28:45.240
Nicknamed "Captain Hook"
owing to the hand he lost

00:28:45.440 --> 00:28:49.480
making an explosive device
in Pakistan,

00:28:49.960 --> 00:28:54.840
Abu Hamza passed himself off as a
veteran, back from the Afghan front.

00:28:56.800 --> 00:28:58.760
When I came to London,

00:28:59.280 --> 00:29:01.280
I was surprised the way some people

00:29:01.920 --> 00:29:05.320
were trying to put themselves
in the journey of jihad

00:29:05.520 --> 00:29:10.600
in order to to recruit, to influence
some young Muslims

00:29:10.800 --> 00:29:13.040
in Britain,

00:29:13.800 --> 00:29:16.400
because as far as you say,

00:29:16.600 --> 00:29:20.320
"Jihad, Afghanistan,
Abdullah Azzam",

00:29:20.640 --> 00:29:22.840
automatically people will come
around you because

00:29:23.040 --> 00:29:26.240
of the influence of the jihad
of Afghanistan.

00:29:26.840 --> 00:29:30.280
So, I was surprised. Some names,

00:29:30.480 --> 00:29:33.040
they were not in Afghanistan!

00:29:34.880 --> 00:29:39.400
Abu Hamza took control of
a mosque in Finsbury Park,

00:29:39.600 --> 00:29:40.960
in northern London.

00:29:42.760 --> 00:29:47.400
This religious building became the
meeting point for nascent groups.

00:29:49.480 --> 00:29:51.160
It was a safe place

00:29:51.360 --> 00:29:53.760
and it was safe in the sense that

00:29:54.520 --> 00:29:59.880
the public authorities didn't care
about what was going on there.

00:30:00.280 --> 00:30:02.040
They kind of had half an eye on it,

00:30:02.240 --> 00:30:04.280
but they thought
it was all a bunch of jokers.

00:30:04.480 --> 00:30:05.480
And in any case,

00:30:05.680 --> 00:30:09.360
joker number one, Abu Hamza,
they could deal with.

00:30:11.320 --> 00:30:14.560
In Great Britain and
many European countries,

00:30:14.760 --> 00:30:18.920
the Londonistan ideologists were
not yet considered a threat,

00:30:19.560 --> 00:30:20.360
but for the French people,

00:30:21.080 --> 00:30:25.280
25 July 1995
was a brutal wake-up call.

00:30:27.520 --> 00:30:30.320
A deadly attack
this afternoon in the heart of Paris

00:30:30.480 --> 00:30:31.680
at Saint-Michel RER station.

00:30:32.400 --> 00:30:36.360
First reports of four dead
and 40 wounded, 16 seriously.

00:30:36.560 --> 00:30:40.440
At 5.30 this afternoon, an explosion
and total darkness,

00:30:40.880 --> 00:30:43.400
screams of horror,
mutilated bodies...

00:30:45.680 --> 00:30:48.240
I was driving a car and stopped
at the side of the road

00:30:48.440 --> 00:30:50.720
because I knew who had struck

00:30:51.160 --> 00:30:52.520
and that it was only
the beginning.

00:30:53.160 --> 00:30:55.640
We understood very quickly
that it was the GIA,

00:30:56.000 --> 00:31:00.320
but we didn't know much about
this new form of terrorism,

00:31:00.520 --> 00:31:02.640
and its religious fundamentalism

00:31:02.840 --> 00:31:04.400
was difficult for us to understand.

00:31:04.720 --> 00:31:07.000
We were confronted
by something quite new.

00:31:08.680 --> 00:31:09.400
ALGIERS, ALGERIA

00:31:09.600 --> 00:31:13.720
This attack was an indirect
consequence of Algerian civil war.

00:31:17.000 --> 00:31:18.640
In 1991,

00:31:18.840 --> 00:31:22.160
the Islamic Salvation Front won
the first round of the elections.

00:31:23.840 --> 00:31:27.560
Its programme was to establish an
Islamic government in the country.

00:31:31.880 --> 00:31:36.040
The government interrupted
the electoral process by force.

00:31:41.920 --> 00:31:45.720
A radical group founded
by Afghan veterans

00:31:45.920 --> 00:31:49.880
took up arms and created
the jihadist organisation GIA.

00:31:53.400 --> 00:31:55.160
They wreaked havoc among
the civilian population,

00:31:55.960 --> 00:31:57.880
wanted to overthrow
the Algerian regime

00:31:58.280 --> 00:32:02.080
and hit out at the former
colonial power, France.

00:32:05.080 --> 00:32:06.400
The French had to be punished

00:32:06.600 --> 00:32:10.480
in the same way
as the Algerian authorities,

00:32:10.920 --> 00:32:12.560
in the minds of the jihadists
at that time,

00:32:12.760 --> 00:32:17.840
because the Algerian government only
held on thanks to the French state.

00:32:20.680 --> 00:32:24.200
At the time, David Vallat was
a committed jihadist

00:32:25.040 --> 00:32:27.320
who supplied the GIA with weapons.

00:32:28.640 --> 00:32:31.080
He decided to leave
the organisation, however,

00:32:31.280 --> 00:32:33.760
when he uncovered
its projects in France.

00:32:37.120 --> 00:32:39.360
After Saint-Michel station in Paris,

00:32:39.560 --> 00:32:41.760
the GIA carried out
a series of attacks

00:32:41.960 --> 00:32:44.520
throughout the summer of 1995,

00:32:47.080 --> 00:32:48.400
until a bomb was set off earlier
than planned

00:32:48.600 --> 00:32:52.160
in front of a Jewish school.

00:32:56.280 --> 00:32:59.400
The explosion could have wreaked
havoc as children were going home.

00:32:59.720 --> 00:33:02.000
One of the terrorists

00:33:04.720 --> 00:33:07.040
was identified:

00:33:08.160 --> 00:33:11.880
Kaled Kelkal, a young Frenchman
of Algerian origin.

00:33:13.240 --> 00:33:14.960
Get out!

00:33:15.160 --> 00:33:16.480
Watch out!

00:33:18.120 --> 00:33:19.600
OK, we're good.

00:33:21.600 --> 00:33:23.720
He was killed by the police,

00:33:24.160 --> 00:33:27.520
the first French terrorist to die
for the jihadist cause.

00:33:35.120 --> 00:33:37.240
The investigation
by two anti-terrorist judges,

00:33:37.400 --> 00:33:39.560
Jean François Ricard
and Jean Louis Bruguière,

00:33:39.760 --> 00:33:41.320
took them to London.

00:33:41.520 --> 00:33:43.000
NEW SCOTLAND YARD

00:33:43.760 --> 00:33:45.800
There were indeed
connections with London

00:33:46.120 --> 00:33:49.840
which showed the transfer
of funds from London

00:33:50.040 --> 00:33:52.800
allowing this action
to take place.

00:33:55.000 --> 00:33:56.640
French investigators and journalists

00:33:56.960 --> 00:34:00.120
discovered Londonistan
and its jihadist ideologies,

00:34:00.840 --> 00:34:02.320
with Omar Bakri at the head.

00:34:04.760 --> 00:34:08.280
Every weekend in London,
Islamists organise meetings.

00:34:08.680 --> 00:34:13.400
That day, the tourist hub
Trafalgar Square was hosting them.

00:34:13.600 --> 00:34:14.520
Algeria was the main topic,

00:34:14.840 --> 00:34:18.760
the rhetoric violent and the
British police officers indifferent.

00:34:19.080 --> 00:34:20.520
With the care of our support,

00:34:20.720 --> 00:34:22.280
manifest us physically,

00:34:22.480 --> 00:34:25.360
financially and verbally,
wherever you are.

00:34:25.560 --> 00:34:28.120
Allah orders us to fight
those who fight us!

00:34:31.400 --> 00:34:35.000
London had become
the European headquarters of the GIA

00:34:35.320 --> 00:34:36.760
and its terrorist activities.

00:34:39.800 --> 00:34:42.920
The GIA had delegated
to their English representatives

00:34:43.120 --> 00:34:46.600
that anything done in their name
in Europe went through them.

00:34:46.800 --> 00:34:50.400
So, they were like the managers of
jihadist administration in Europe.

00:34:50.800 --> 00:34:51.680
I take no glory in that,

00:34:51.880 --> 00:34:55.480
but, chronologically, we were,
my generation,

00:34:55.680 --> 00:35:00.440
the first to have established jihad
as an international movement.

00:35:03.920 --> 00:35:05.520
The Finsbury Park mosque

00:35:05.720 --> 00:35:09.160
and its imam Abu Hamza,
the so-called "Captain Hook",

00:35:09.360 --> 00:35:12.480
played a central role among
the Algerian jihadist groups.

00:35:14.360 --> 00:35:15.880
Abu Hamza at that point

00:35:16.080 --> 00:35:20.040
had aligned himself
with the GIA in Algeria.

00:35:20.400 --> 00:35:21.800
The French security service started

00:35:21.960 --> 00:35:24.240
to speak to the British
security services and say:

00:35:24.440 --> 00:35:26.720
"Do you know
this guy is a menace?

00:35:26.920 --> 00:35:28.120
What are you going to do about it?"

00:35:28.320 --> 00:35:30.080
The British security services said:

00:35:30.280 --> 00:35:32.400
"We're not going to do anything
about it, it's not our problem!"

00:35:32.720 --> 00:35:35.800
I know there was
a certain amount of concern,

00:35:36.000 --> 00:35:39.320
particularly on the part of
the French authorities and I know

00:35:39.520 --> 00:35:42.440
Juge Brugière has expressed this
many times,

00:35:42.640 --> 00:35:46.200
he was concerned that we weren't
being robust enough in London

00:35:46.400 --> 00:35:50.120
in dealing with people he described
very clearly as terrorists,

00:35:50.680 --> 00:35:51.800
but it wasn't clear at all
at that time that

00:35:52.000 --> 00:35:56.520
they were actually committing any
terrorist offences in the UK,

00:35:56.720 --> 00:35:59.520
nor that they posed a direct threat
to the British public.

00:36:02.720 --> 00:36:06.120
The place of worship
awakened the curiosity of

00:36:06.680 --> 00:36:09.080
journalist Kurt Barling.

00:36:10.040 --> 00:36:12.920
When we filmed undercover
in Finsbury Park mosque

00:36:13.120 --> 00:36:14.840
and we discovered
that there were young boys

