DENMARK

00:37:09.200 --> 00:37:11.560
Partisans established themselves
in Europe.

00:37:13.920 --> 00:37:17.960
They took part in the birth of
a new generation of terrorists.

00:37:23.120 --> 00:37:27.480
These individuals set up some
of the first jihadist networks

00:37:27.680 --> 00:37:29.200
in Europe at the time.

00:37:29.920 --> 00:37:31.400
We're talking about small numbers,

00:37:31.600 --> 00:37:35.040
but in some cases, very charismatic
individuals,

00:37:35.240 --> 00:37:37.720
which slowly attracted people
around them

00:37:37.920 --> 00:37:42.120
and so started radicalising some
first or second-generation Muslims.

00:37:47.640 --> 00:37:52.040
In Denmark, a handful of ideologists
thus broadcast a radical Islam

00:37:52.240 --> 00:37:54.440
from the beginning of the 1990s.

00:37:59.080 --> 00:38:00.040
Nothing predisposed this country

00:38:00.240 --> 00:38:04.560
to become one of the strongholds
of European jihadism.

00:38:07.040 --> 00:38:09.520
Denmark has no colonial history
in the Middle East,

00:38:10.800 --> 00:38:13.280
it is on the margins
of its geopolitical issues

00:38:14.600 --> 00:38:18.440
and its social model is touted
as one of the best in the world.

00:38:20.000 --> 00:38:24.480
You had a situation in Denmark in
the '90s where it was very liberal

00:38:24.680 --> 00:38:28.760
and you didn't have
these strict control systems

00:38:28.960 --> 00:38:30.320
that you have today.

00:38:30.640 --> 00:38:33.760
So, you had asylum seekers
coming in

00:38:34.920 --> 00:38:40.040
