from four army officers.

00:39:43.120 --> 00:39:45.640
The assassins claimed to be from
a terrorist group seeking

00:39:45.960 --> 00:39:48.600
to establish a khalifat in Egypt.

00:39:52.720 --> 00:39:56.000
Abu Talal was part of the plan

00:39:56.200 --> 00:39:58.520
to take Anwar el-Sadat
off power,

00:39:58.720 --> 00:40:02.480
and it was his friends who
actually shot Anwar el-Sadat.

00:40:07.480 --> 00:40:10.240
Abu Talal, like hundreds
of militant Islamists,

00:40:10.840 --> 00:40:13.240
was arrested
by the Egyptian police.

00:40:14.560 --> 00:40:17.440
During the trial, which began
in December 1982,

00:40:18.280 --> 00:40:19.480
he can be seen here

00:40:19.680 --> 00:40:23.400
alongside one of the major figures
of contemporary jihadism:

00:40:24.160 --> 00:40:28.320
Omar Abdel Rahman,
nicknamed "The Blind Sheikh",

00:40:28.520 --> 00:40:31.600
one of the leaders of the
Egyptian terrorist organisation.

00:40:37.480 --> 00:40:39.080
During this lengthy trial,

00:40:39.240 --> 00:40:41.840
which became
a forum for these fundamentalists,

00:40:42.040 --> 00:40:44.040
one man was
already standing out:

00:40:45.240 --> 00:40:49.360
Ayman Al-Zawahiri, bin Laden's
future right-hand man

00:40:49.560 --> 00:40:51.160
and Al Qaeda's number two.

00:40:54.120 --> 00:40:55.720
We believe in our religion both

00:40:55.920 --> 00:40:59.200
as an ideology and practice and
hence we have

00:40:59.400 --> 00:41:01.920
tried our best to establish

00:41:02.120 --> 00:41:05.040
this Islamic state
and Islamic society.

00:41:05.720 --> 00:41:07.040
In spite of his young age,
Abu Talal had already met

00:41:07.240 --> 00:41:12.040
the most outstanding personalities
of the jihadist movement.

00:41:17.880 --> 00:41:21.440
Freed, he went to
the Afghan-Pakistani border

00:41:21.640 --> 00:41:23.640
where he met bin Laden.

00:41:23.960 --> 00:41:27.600
He only stayed there a few months
at the beginning of the 1990s.

00:41:29.120 --> 00:41:33.240
And he came to Denmark in 1993

00:41:33.440 --> 00:41:36.960
and very quickly, he became
a central figure

00:41:37.160 --> 00:41:41.640
also in the Islamic
extremist environment.

00:41:46.600 --> 00:41:50.160
The Egyptian had understood the
media's importance for his ideas.

00:41:54.080 --> 00:41:57.840
He filmed his conferences and
produced VHS cassettes.

00:42:00.880 --> 00:42:02.360
He even managed to pull himself up
alongside some

00:42:02.560 --> 00:42:06.000
